source: knowledge_base: topic - chatbot_identity; content - I am TK-Bot, a personal AI assistant for Tarun Karnati's portfolio. I am designed to provide fast and accurate information about his skills, projects, and experience to recruiters and visitors. My knowledge comes directly from his professional data.
knowledge_base: topic - contact_primary_email; content - The best and most direct way to contact Tarun is by sending an email to tarunk1109@gmail.com.
knowledge_base: topic - contact_linkedin; content - You can connect with Tarun on his LinkedIn profile here: https://linkedin.com/in/tarun-karnati-84a95623b.
knowledge_base: topic - contact_github; content - You can view Tarun's code and projects on his GitHub profile: https://github.com/Tarunk1109.

knowledge_base: topic - resume_download; content - Yes, a downloadable PDF of Tarun's resume is available directly on the portfolio website. As the AI bot, I can't provide the file directly, but you can find the link on the main page.

knowledge_base: topic - career_objective_and_availability; content - Tarun is actively seeking full-time and co-op opportunities in Software Development. He is especially interested in roles focused on full-stack development or AI integration, where he can help build innovative and impactful software solutions.

knowledge_base: topic - work_authorization_canada; content - Yes, Tarun is fully eligible to work in Canada. As a postgraduate student at Humber College, he is actively seeking co-op and full-time roles.

knowledge_base: topic - professional_summary_overview; content - Tarun Karnati is an aspiring Full-Stack Developer based in Toronto, Canada. He specializes in building robust, end-to-end applications with integrated AI features. His expertise lies in using Java and Spring Boot for scalable backend systems and modern JavaScript, HTML, and CSS for responsive frontends.

knowledge_base: topic - development_best_practices; content - Tarun applies development best practices in his work, including MVC Architecture for organized code, implementing proper User Authentication for security, and detailed error handling to create robust applications.

knowledge_base: topic - education_humber_college; content - Tarun is a postgraduate student in the Information Technology Solutions program at Humber College in Toronto (expected 2025-2026). He has distinguished himself academically by earning a spot on the Dean's Honour List for Semester 1, 2025.
knowledge_base: topic - education_bachelors_degree; content - Tarun holds a Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science from the SRK Institute of Technology, India (2020-2024).
knowledge_base: topic - skills_core_languages; content - Tarun's core programming languages include Java, Python, C, JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3, SQL, and Bash.

knowledge_base: topic - skills_frameworks_databases; content - For frameworks and data, Tarun's expertise includes Spring Boot, Node.js, MongoDB, and MySQL. He is also highly proficient with Git and GitHub for version control.

knowledge_base: topic - skills_ai_deployment; content - In AI and Deployment, Tarun has hands-on experience with GenAI concepts like RAG and fine-tuning, using tools like LangChain and the OpenAI API. He is skilled in deployment using Docker, Postman, Netlify, and Heroku.

knowledge_base: topic - technical_interests; content - Tarun is passionate about Full-Stack Web Development, building AI and Chatbot Systems, Cloud Integration and Deployment (CI/CD), Data-Driven Software Solutions, and exploring new frameworks and APIs to stay at the forefront of technology.

knowledge_base: topic - project_perkpal_overview; content - Perkpal is a full-stack web application that provides personalized discounts and coupons to specific communities like students and seniors. It's a complete, end-to-end project that showcases Tarun's ability to build a functional product with features like user registration, login, and categorization.

knowledge_base: topic - project_perkpal_tech_stack; content - The Perkpal project was built with a modern tech stack: a Java and Spring Boot backend, a MongoDB database for flexible data storage, and a user interface created with JavaScript, HTML, and CSS.
knowledge_base: topic - project_perkpal_repo_link; content - Yes, the GitHub repository for the Perkpal project is available here: https://github.com/Tarunk1109/PerkPal.

knowledge_base: topic - project_iot_overview; content - The IoT Women's Safety Device is a hardware and software project designed as a real-time tracking and emergency alert system. The prototype can track a user's location and send alerts, demonstrating skills beyond traditional web development.

knowledge_base: topic - project_iot_leadership_role; content - Tarun took a leadership role in the IoT safety device project, guiding a small team of four. He was responsible for the overall system architecture, programming the device in Python, and ensuring the successful integration of all components.

knowledge_base: topic - project_nlp_overview; content - Tarun's NLP project focused on sentiment analysis. He built a system that analyzed thousands of product reviews to extract valuable business insights. This research was formally published in the IJCRT journal, highlighting his ability to produce high-quality academic and practical work.

knowledge_base: topic - project_nlp_publication_link; content - The publication for Tarun's NLP project can be viewed in the IJCRT journal at this link: http://ijcrt.org/viewfull.php?&p_id=IJCRT2405210.
knowledge_base: topic - publication_dcnn_springer; content - Tarun also has a publication titled 'Fabric Defect Segmentation (DCNN)' from the IPDIMS 2023 Conference, published by Springer.

knowledge_base: topic - certification_docker; content - Tarun holds a 'Docker Foundations Professional' certification from LinkedIn. The certificate can be verified here: https://www.linkedin.com/learning/certificates/eb103cef361f6d528bfa297c6d730fb6579041cb4dc626e91377a9269aca1e39?u=2218586.

knowledge_base: topic - certification_microsoft_software_dev; content - He has earned the 'Career Essentials in Software Development' certification from Microsoft and LinkedIn. Verify it here: https://www.linkedin.com/learning/certificates/0a5fb95f1f2ab199e4ba32cbd91c56f8d8ba092a44026604ef8aa4b12d11a428?u=2218586.
knowledge_base: topic - certification_python; content - Tarun is certified in 'PCAP: Programming Essentials in Python' from the Cisco Networking Academy.

knowledge_base: topic - certification_ai_for_everyone; content - He also holds the 'AI for Everyone' certification from Coursera, which can be verified here: https://www.coursera.org/account/accomplishments/verify/DHL7Z3VDD96C.
knowledge_base: topic - experience_virtual_internship_aws; content - Tarun gained practical experience through a virtual internship with AWS, focused on Cloud Architecture and Data Analytics.
knowledge_base: topic - experience_workshops; content - He has further honed his skills by participating in hands-on workshops for IoT System Design and Data Visualization with Tableau and PowerBI.

knowledge_base: topic - behavioral_full_stack_project_example; content - When asked about building a project from scratch, Tarun can point to Perkpal. Situation: He wanted to build a real-world application. Task: Create a full-stack personalized discount platform. Action: He designed the MongoDB schema, developed the Spring Boot REST APIs, built the responsive frontend, and deployed it. Result: A fully functional application that demonstrates his end-to-end development capabilities.

knowledge_base: topic - behavioral_leadership_example; content - As the lead on the IoT Safety Device project, Tarun was responsible for delegating tasks and managing timelines. When the team faced a critical bug in the GPS module, he organized a debugging session, systematically isolated the problem, and guided the team to implement a software patch, ensuring the project stayed on track and was completed successfully.

knowledge_base: topic - strengths_as_developer; content - Tarun's key strengths are his solid foundation in full-stack development, his proactive problem-solving mindset, and his genuine passion for integrating AI into practical applications. He is a quick learner who is always exploring new technologies to improve his skill set.

knowledge_base: topic - portfolio_website_features; content - This portfolio website itself is a project. It features a dark/light mode toggle for user preference and this interactive AI chatbot, TK-Bot, to provide information efficiently.
